Here I have used a 2D array with **2 rows and 26 Columns** so that there occurrence can be stored in **row 1** with all corresponding **characters repetitions** and **row 2** with there last **occurrence index**. Finally I iterate through the 2D array and find the **first unique char with only one occurrences**.

**Time Complexity -> O(n)**
**Space Complexity-> O(1)**(because linear array)

class Solution {
public:
    int firstUniqChar(string s) {
        int arr[2][27] = {0}; 
        int num=0;
        for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++)
        {
            num=s[i]-'a';
            arr[0][num]+=1;
            arr[1][num]=i;
        }
        int small=99999;         // Storing maximum value that can possibly occur.
        for(int i=0;i<26;i++)
        {
            if(arr[0][i]==1)
            {
                if(arr[1][i]<small && arr[1][i]>=0)
                {
                    small=arr[1][i];
                }
            }
        }
        if(small==99999)
            return -1;
        return small;
    }
};

